n bishop, about whom a large number of legends grew up, and who was venerated in the Orthodox Church as well as the Catholic. In North America, the English form of the surname has absorbed cognates from other languages and also their patronymics and other derivatives, e.g. Croatian and Serbian <b>Nikolić</b> (see   Nikolic  ), Greek <b>Papanikolaou</b> ‘(son of) Nicholas the priest’ and   Nikolopoulos  . Compare   Nickolas  .","History: The colonial official and revolutionary patriot Robert Carter Nicholas was from a prominent VA family on both sides. His father was a British navy surgeon who emigrated <i>c.</i> 1700 from Lancashire, England, to Williamsburg, VA."]},{"name":"Neilsen","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Scandinavian Erik, Ejnar, Gurli, Jorgen, Nels, Niels.","Americanized form of Danish, Norwegian, and North German   Nielsen  . Compare   Neilson   3.","Scottish (Midlothian): variant of   Neilson   1."]},{"name":"Nelsen","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Scandinavian Nels, Erik, Einer, Berger, Folmer, Holger, Iver, Juel, Morten, Thor, Uffe.","Americanized form of Danish, Norwegian, and North German   Nielsen   or   Nilsen  . Compare   Nelson  .","Flemish and German: patronymic from   Nelis  ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1353273,"age":48,"year":"1350","julianDay":2214138,"description":"Plague ravishes Denmark and Sweden.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1353274,"age":95,"year":"1397","julianDay":2231305,"description":"The Union of Kalmar unites Denmark, Sweden and Norway.","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Yliama N. Nielsen was born in 1302, in Roskilde, Denmark. She married Niels Jacobsen Rud about 1329. They were the parents of at least 3 sons and 1 daughter. She died in Denmark."},"et":{"1302–":"1302–Surnud","1300–1358":"1300–1358","1315–Female":"1315–Surnud","1330–1387":"1330–1387","1332–1403":"1332–1403","1334–1372":"1334–1372","1302–Female":"1302–Surnud","1330":"1330","ABT 1334":"umbes 1334","1350":"1350","1372":"1372","ABT